{
    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{10, 18, 15, -5, -14, -21\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data set\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{10 + 18 + 15 + (-5) + (-14) + (-21)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{10 + 18 + 15 - 5 - 14 - 21}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{10 + 18 + 15 = 43; 43 - 5 = 38; 38 - 14 = 24; 24 - 21 = 3}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{3}{6} = 0.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Subtract the mean from each data point and square the result\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(10 - 0.5)^2 &= 9.5^2 = 90.25 \\\\\n(18 - 0.5)^2 &= 17.5^2 = 306.25 \\\\\n(15 - 0.5)^2 &= 14.5^2 = 210.25 \\\\\n(-5 - 0.5)^2 &= (-5.5)^2 = 30.25 \\\\\n(-14 - 0.5)^2 &= (-14.5)^2 = 210.25 \\\\\n(-21 - 0.5)^2 &= (-21.5)^2 = 462.25 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared differences\n\n$$\n90.25 + 306.25 + 210.25 + 30.25 + 210.25 + 462.25 = 1248.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1 = 5$ (since it's a sample)\n\n$$\n\\text{Variance} = \\frac{1248.5}{5}"
}